===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
Unclear; probably a {{liushu|p|nocap=1}}.

{{zh-ref|Guo (1954)}} suggests that it represents a thumb and is original form of {{och-l|拇}} or, more probably, {{och-l|擘}}.

Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Unger (''apud'' Schuessler, 2007)}} suggests that it represents an acorn, noting its use in {{zh-l|*樂|oak}} (= {{zh-l|*櫟}}) and {{zh-l|*皂|acorn}}.

===Etymology===
STEDT derives it from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*bawk||white}}, whence also {{cog|tbq-bdg-pro|*bok||white}}, {{cog|lif|tr=phɔ|t=white}}; also compare {{cog|mkh-pro|*kɓɔɔk||white, grey}}.

However, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} finds it difficult to reconcile these forms with {{cog|ltc|-}} due to the lack of medial ''r''. Instead, he proposes a derivation from {{der|zh|sit-pro|*(p/b/h)(w/j)a(ː)(r/l/n/t)|*bar|white}} with ''-k'' extension, thus cognate with {{och-l|皤|white|id=2}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}), {{cog|lus|vâr||(to be) white}}, {{cog|kar-pro|*ʔ(b)wa||white}}.

